Chicken Korma
Judy Heumann

12 pieces of chicken or 2 fryers, cut up
3 cups plain yogurt
4 tsp curry
2 tsp ground corriander
1 tsp ginger
6 cloves garlic, minced
black pepper
1 tbsp lemon juice
2 tbsp oil
2 medium onions, chopped
2 bay leaves

Remove skinds from chicken.  In a large bowl, combine yogurt, curry, corriander, ginger, garlic, pepper and lemon juice.  Add chicken pieces and stir to coat.  Cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes or more.  Heat oil in a large pot.  Add onion and cook until soft.  Add bay leaves, chicken and yogurt marinade to the pot. Mix well.  Bring to a boil, then simmer over medium heat for 45 minutes.  Stir periodically.

Serves 6.
